## Phase 5: Optimization Suggestion Engine (Rule-Based)

### 5.1 Code-Level Rules (Regex Analysis)
- Build a service `OptimizationEngine`. Function `analyzeQueryString(sql)`:
  - Regex test `/\bSELECT\s+\*/i`. Push Warning: `"Avoid using SELECT *. Specify exact columns to minimize network and memory overhead."`
  - Regex test `/\bWHERE\b/i`. If missing in large tables, push Warning: `"No WHERE clause detected; query will scan entire table."`

### 5.2 Tree-Level Rules (Performance Analysis)
- Function `analyzePlanTree(parsedRoot)`: Flatten the tree for linear iteration.
- Loop flattened nodes:
  - **Sequential Scan on Large Data**: If `nodeType === 'Seq Scan'` AND `estimatedRows > 1000`, push `"Sequential scanning massive row limits. Indexing highly recommended."`
  - **Expensive Loops**: If `nodeType === 'Nested Loop'` AND `actualLoops > 10000`, push `"Nested loop executed too many times. Investigate join conditions."`
  - **Cost Dominator**: Calculate tree total cost. Flag any single node contributing `>70%` of the `totalCost`.

### 5.3 Persisting Suggestions
- Execute `prisma.optimizationSuggestion.createMany()` mapping the suggestions array to the parent `Query.id`.
- Return to the frontend to render sequentially in a "Suggestions" sidebar.

